# Windows Batch Path Consistency

All batch scripts must prepend the following to %PATH% at runtime:

```
set "PATH=%SystemRoot%\System32;%SystemRoot%;%SystemRoot%\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\;%PATH%"
```

This ensures commands like `netstat`, `findstr`, `timeout`, and `powershell` are always available, regardless of the shell or environment. This pattern prevents failures when running scripts from Cursor, Git Bash, or other non-standard shells.

## Example

```bat
@echo off
REM Ensure Windows system commands available
set "PATH=%SystemRoot%\System32;%SystemRoot%;%SystemRoot%\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\;%PATH%"
REM ...rest of script...
```

## Maintenance
- Apply this pattern to all new and existing batch scripts in the project.
- Reference this rule in script comments and documentation as needed.
